('20487', '1', 'Place pork, fat side up, in large glass baking dish. Rub pork with salt and pepper.'),
('20487', '2', 'Whisk honey, 4 tablespoons lemon juice, 4 tablespoons olive oil, coriander, and thyme in small bowl.'),
('20487', '3', 'Pour over pork; cover pork loosely with foil.'),
('20487', '4', 'Let stand at room temperature 1 hour, basting occasionally.'),
('20487', '5', 'Preheat oven to 375°F.'),
('20487', '6', 'Transfer pork to roasting pan; reserve marinade. Roast pork 15 minutes. Spoon 1/4 of reserved marinade over pork.'),
('20487', '7', 'Add 1/4 cup broth to roasting pan. Roast pork 15 minutes; spoon remaining marinade over.'),
('20487', '8', 'Add 1/4 cup broth to pan. Roast until instant-read thermometer inserted into center of pork registers 150°F, about 40 minutes longer.'),
('20487', '9', 'Add 1/4 cup broth to pan, stirring browned bits from bottom.'),
('20487', '10', 'Transfer pork to platter; tent with foil. Strain pan juices into 1-cup measuring cup; add enough broth to measure 1 cup liquid.'),
('20487', '11', 'Pour into small saucepan; keep warm over low heat.'),
('20487', '12', 'Heat remaining 3 tablespoons oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.'),
('20487', '13', 'Add chard and toss to coat. Cover and cook until chard is tender, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.'),
('20487', '14', 'Mix in remaining lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('20487', '15', 'Spread greens on platter. Slice pork and arrange atop greens.'),
('20487', '16', 'Pour pan juices over.'),
('20488', '1', 'Preheat the oven to 42'),
('20488', '2', 'Brush the leek with 1 teaspoon of the olive oil and arrange on 1 side of a large baking sheet, cut side down. On the other side, toss the squash with 2 teaspoons of the olive oil. Season the vegetables with salt and pepper and roast for 20 minutes, or until golden and just tender.'),
('20488', '3', 'Cut the leek into 1-inch lengths.'),
('20488', '4', 'Meanwhile, heat 1 tablespoon of the oil in a 14- to 16-inch paella pan or skillet. Season the chicken with salt and pepper; cook over moderate heat until golden, 10 minutes.'),
('20488', '5', 'Transfer to a plate.'),
('20488', '6', 'Add the onion and the remaining 2 tablespoons of oil to the pan; cook over low heat until softened.'),
('20488', '7', 'Add the chorizo, saffron and cayenne; cook over moderately high heat, stirring, for 2 minutes.'),
('20488', '8', 'Add the rice and 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt; cook, stirring, for 2 minutes. Stir in the stock, tomatoes, chard, leek and squash.'),
('20488', '9', 'Nestle the chicken into the rice, skin side up. Simmer the paella over low heat for 5 minutes.'),
('20488', '10', 'Transfer to a 350 oven and bake for 30 minutes, or until the stock is absorbed, the rice is tender and the chicken is cooked through.'),
('20488', '11', 'Remove from the oven and cover with a towel; let stand for 10 minutes.'),
('20488', '12', 'Serve at once.'),
('20490', '1', 'In a small skillet, melt butter and saut the almonds until they begin to turn golden.'),
('20490', '2', 'Remove from the pan with a slotted spoon and salt lightly.'),
('20490', '3', 'Toss the greens with the vinaigrette and divide among six plates. Sprinkle with the warm almonds and grate a little goat cheese over each salad.'),
('20490', '4', 'Serve.'),
