('20492', '1', 'Make the pasta dough. Sift the flour into a mound on a counter and make a well in the center. Break the eggs into the well and add the oil and a pinch of salt. Knead to a soft dough, shape into a ball, cover with a clean dish towel, and let rest for 30 minutes.'),
('20492', '2', 'Meanwhile, make the filling. Cook the potatoes in lightly salted boiling water for 15-20 minutes until tender.'),
('20492', '3', 'Drain and mash. Cook the chard leaves in just enough boiling water to cover for 5-10 minutes until tender.'),
('20492', '4', 'Drain, squeeze out the excess liquid, and chop. Melt the butter in a pan.'),
('20492', '5', 'Add the garlic and parsley and cook over low heat, stirring frequently for a few minutes.'),
('20492', '6', 'Add the leek and sausage and cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.'),
('20492', '7', 'Remove the pan from the heat and let cool.'),
('20492', '8', 'Combine the sausage mixture, mashed potatoes, chard, bread crumbs, Parmesan, and egg in a bowl and season to taste with salt and pepper.'),
('20492', '9', 'Roll out the dough on a lightly floured counter into a thin sheet.'),
('20492', '10', 'Cut out rectangles about 3 1/4 x 6 1/4 inches. Put a mound of filling on each one, roll the dough up, and press the edges well to seal, then gently bend into a horseshoe shape. Cook the casônsèi in plenty of salted boiling water for 5 minutes until al dente.'),
('20492', '11', 'Drain, transfer to a warmed serving dish, pour the melted butter over them, and sprinkle with Parmesan.'),
('20492', '12', 'Serve immediately.'),
('20492', '13', 'From The Silver Spoon: Pasta. © 2009 Phaidon Press Limited. Published in the United States of America by Phaidon Press Limited.'),
('20496', '1', 'Cook the farro according to package instructions. The brand I use calls for a 25 minute simmer in a quart of salted water.'),
('20496', '2', 'Drain the farro, dump it into a big bowl, and toss with 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar while it is still warm.'),
('20496', '3', 'Steam the chard leaves.'),
('20496', '4', 'Put them, still wet from rinsing, into a saucepan and add an extra splash of water. Cover, turn the heat to medium, and cook until they are tender enough to eat but not mushy. Peek in every once in a while to toss the leaves with a spoon and taste for doneness; it usually takes around 5 minutes.'),
('20496', '5', 'Drain in a colander. When cool enough to handle, chop.'),
('20496', '6', 'Cook the carrot and chard stems.'),
('20496', '7', 'Put them in the saucepan you used for the chard leaves with a glug of olive oil and the garlic. If there is still chard-cooking liquid in the saucepan, that''s fine. Turn the heat to medium-low and saute gently, adjusting the heat if necessary, until the vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.'),
('20496', '8', 'Toss the farro, chopped chard leaves, chard stems, and carrots together in a big bowl.'),
('20496', '9', 'Drizzle with 1 tablespoon red wine vinegar and 2 tablespoons olive oil. Season with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; toss again and taste.'),
('20496', '10', 'Add more oil or salt and pepper if necessary.'),
('20496', '11', 'Serve warmish, room temperature, or cold with about an ounce of feta cheese and a few olives per person.'),
('20499', '1', 'Prepare soup by combining 1/4 cup whole wheat flour, cumin and salt in a small bowl. Break off teaspoon-sized chunks of ground turkey and lightly dredge them in flour mixture.'),
('20499', '2', 'Heat olive oil in a saut pan over medium heat.'),
('20499', '3', 'Add turkey chunks and brown them on all sides. Do not worry about cooking them fully, as they will finish cooking in the soup. Set aside.Melt butter in a large soup pot over medium-high heat.'),
('20499', '4', 'Add carrots, celery and onions and cook for about 5 minutes, until fragrant and starting to turn translucent.'),
('20499', '5', 'Add remaining 2 tablespoons whole wheat flour and cook, stirring constantly, until flour starts to lightly brown. Stir in chicken broth, water, cumin, black-eyed peas and browned turkey chunks and bring to a simmer, 7 to 10 minutes.'),
('20499', '6', 'Add red pepper, zucchini and Swiss chard and bring soup to a rapid simmer, 4 to 5 minutes.Meanwhile, make dumplings.'),
('20499', '7', 'Combine cornmeal, baking powder, eggs, flour, salt, milk, scallions and jalapeo in a small mixing bowl.'),
('20499', '8', 'Mix until well combined.Drop tablespoons of cornbread batter into the simmering soup. Space them out so they do not stick together while cooking. Cook uncovered for about 5 minutes. Reduce heat, cover, and cook gently for 15 minutes. Test that dumplings are fully cooked before serving.'),
('20501', '1', 'Stir in 4 cups broth, sweet potatoes, lentils and bay leaf. Increase heat to high and bring to a boil; reduce heat to medium, partially cover, and simmer for 25 minutes. (If lentils seem dry, add up to 1 cup stock, as needed.) Stir in chard and salt and pepper, and continue cooking until lentils are tender and chard is cooked, about 30 to 45 minutes total.'),
('20501', '2', 'Just before serving, stir in cilantro, lime zest and juice. Spoon into a large, shallow serving dish.'),
('20501', '3', 'Garnish with almonds if desired and scallions.See more: Beans, Indian, Photo, Potatoes, Vegan, Vegetarian'),
('20501', '4', 'Do more: Link | Bookmark| Pin | Print| Email| 190 Comments'),
('20503', '1', 'Cook bacon in a large skillet over medium heat until crisp.'),
('20503', '2', 'Add onion, garlic, and mushrooms to pan; cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently. Set aside.'),
('20503', '3', 'Remove and discard giblets and neck from chicken.'),
('20503', '4', 'Place chicken and thyme in a large Dutch oven over medium heat. Cover with 4 1/2 quarts cold water; bring to a simmer. Skim fat from surface; discard.'),
('20503', '5', 'Remove stems and center ribs from Swiss chard. Coarsely chop stems and ribs; reserve leaves.'),
('20503', '6', 'Add stems, ribs, and next 5 ingredients (through apple) to pan; bring to a simmer. Pierce habanero with a fork; add to pan. Cook 35 minutes or until chicken is done.'),
('20503', '7', 'Remove chicken from pan; cool slightly.'),
('20503', '8', 'Remove chicken from bones; chop meat. Discard bones, thyme sprig, and habanero. Strain barley mixture through a sieve over a bowl. Reserve 4 cups of broth for another use. Return remaining 6 cups broth to pan; bring to a boil. Cook 10 minutes. Return chicken and barley mixture to pan; bring to a simmer.'),
('20503', '9', 'Add mushroom mixture. Cook 2 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Stir in 3/4 teaspoon salt and black pepper.'),
('20503', '10', 'To prepare pesto, cook Swiss chard leaves in boiling water 2 minutes.'),
('20503', '11', 'Drain and rinse under cold water; drain.'),
('20503', '12', 'Place leaves, walnuts, and remaining ingredients in a food processor; process until smooth.'),
('20503', '13', 'Serve with soup.'),
('20510', '1', 'In a large, heavy stockpot or Dutch oven, heat olive oil over medium-high flame and add shallots, onions, leeks and garlic. Saut for a few minutes and throw in a big pinch of sea salt, the rosemary, ground fennel seeds, chile and bay leaf, and cook for a few minutes more.'),
('20510', '2', 'Add all the rest of the vegetables except the tomatoes and stir to coat with the oil. After a few minutes, add the tomatoes, their juice, the stock or water and the parmesan rinds.'),
('20510', '3', 'Simmer until vegetables are tender but not mushy, about 30 minutes. Season to taste with sea salt and freshly ground black pepper. If youre adding meatballs, the time to do it is now. Poach them gently in in the hot soup for about 15 minutes.'),
('20510', '4', 'Serve the soup with any or all of the following garnishes: a drizzle of good olive oil, a little grated Parmesan, a scattering of fresh herbs, some toasted croutons.'),
('20513', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('20513', '2', 'Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F.'),
('20513', '3', 'Cut out the stems from peppers and discard.'),
('20513', '4', 'Remove the seeds and clean out the white ribs. Season them inside with salt and pepper. Rub the outsides of the peppers with vegetable oil and place them, stem side down, onto a baking sheet.'),
('20513', '5', 'Bake them for 30 minutes, or until the skins are wrinkled and slightly charred.'),
('20513', '6', 'Remove the peppers from the oven and put them into a large bowl. Cover the bowl with plastic wrap and let them steam until they are cool enough to handle, about 10 minutes. Peel the skin from the peppers, making sure to keep them whole, and set aside.'),
('20513', '7', 'While the peppers are baking and steaming, make the pesto: Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Have a bowl of ice water ready. When the water is boiling, add the basil leaves. After 5 seconds (yes, 5 seconds) remove the basil and immediately put it into the ice water. (This will keep the pesto green.) When it is cold, drain the basil and squeeze out any excess water.'),
('20513', '8', 'Put the basil into a food processor or blender and add the pine nuts, cheese, and garlic. Turn on the processor and slowly add the olive oil until the mixture is smooth. Refrigerate until ready to use.'),
('20513', '9', 'In a large skillet over high heat, melt 2 tablespoons of the butter. Cook the eggplant until beginning to soften, about 5 minutes.'),
('20513', '10', 'Add the onions and cook until softened and lightly browned, about 10 minutes more.'),
('20513', '11', 'Transfer them to a cutting board, let them cool a bit, and chop them finely with a knife.'),
('20513', '12', 'Add 1 tablespoon butter to the same pan over medium-high heat. When it is melted, add the Swiss chard, cover the pan, and let the chard wilt for about 1 minute.'),
('20513', '13', 'Transfer the chard to a bowl.'),
('20513', '14', 'Add the vegetables, ricotta, 1 tablespoon of the pesto, and season with salt and pepper.'),
('20513', '15', 'Mix well, taste, and adjust the seasoning. Stuff this mixture into the peppers, being careful to keep them whole.'),
('20513', '16', 'Place them on their sides into a lightly buttered baking dish. Sprinkle each pepper evenly with bread crumbs and bake until the tops are golden brown, about 10 minutes.'),
('20513', '17', 'Serve immediately garnished with extra pesto.'),
('20515', '1', 'For the White Bean Chicken Chile Verde:Preheat oven to 425 degrees F. Line a large baking or cookie sheet with foil. Set aside.'),
('20515', '2', 'Remove skins from tomatillos. Wash, dry, and cut in half.'),
('20515', '3', 'Place cut side down on foil lined baking sheet. Wash and cut poblanos in half, remove ribbing, seeds and stems.'),
('20515', '4', 'Place cut side down (skins facing up) on the baking sheet.'),
('20515', '5', 'Drizzle the tomatillos and poblanos with olive oil. Roast at 425 degrees F until tomatillos are soft and the chiles are blistered.'),
('20515', '6', 'Add cooked tomatillos and poblanos (you can skin them if you want, but I opted not to) in a food processor and puree until smooth. Set aside.'),
('20515', '7', 'Heat the 2 teaspoons of olive oil in a large dutch oven or stock pot.'),
('20515', '8', 'Add the onion and saute until golden and tender, about 5 minutes.'),
('20515', '9', 'Add the garlic, oregano, cumin and chili powder.'),
('20515', '10', 'Saute for an additional 3 minutes. Stir the tomatillo mixture, cook over medium-low heat (lowering heat if sputtering occurs) for 10 minutes, until thickened. Stir in the broth, beans (with liquid) and shredded chicken. Continue to simmer for an additional 20 minutes.Stir in the chopped chard, season to taste with salt and pepper, and simmer for 5-10 more minutes, until chard is tender.'),
('20515', '11', 'Serve topped with cilantro lime pesto, sour cream, tortilla chips and diced avocado.For the Cilantro-Lime Pesto'),
('20515', '12', 'Add all ingredients to a food processor and blend until smooth. Season to taste with salt and pepper, if desired.'),
('20517', '1', 'Wash the chard stalks in cold water. (See note below about using the chard leaves.) Bring 3 quarts water to a boil, drop in the stalks, and cook at a moderate boil until they feel tender when prodded with a fork, approximately 30 minutes, depending on the stalks.'),
('20517', '2', 'Drain and set aside.'),
('20517', '3', 'Put the olive oil and garlic in a saut pan, turn on the heat to medium. Cook and stir the garlic until it becomes very lightly colored, then add the boiled stalks, the parsley, salt, and pepper. Turn the heat up to medium high, tossing and turning the stalks to coat them well. Cook for about 5 minutes, then transfer the contents of the pan to a warm plate and serve at once.'),
('20517', '4', 'var article'),
