('20518', '1', 'Preheat oven to 350F.'),
('20518', '2', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a large pan on medium high heat.'),
('20518', '3', 'Add potato, onion, pepper and fennel; saut until soft, about 3 minutes.'),
('20518', '4', 'Add garlic; saut until golden, about 2 minutes. Stir in chard and spinach; cook 2 minutes or until wilted.'),
('20518', '5', 'Transfer to a bowl and cool. Beat eggs in another bowl. Stir eggs, feta, cottage cheese, soymilk, breadcrumbs, cilantro, dil,l and chives into veggie mix. Fold in crabmeat. Season with salt and pepper. Coat a 9" x 12" pan with cooking spray; dust with 2 tbsp Parmesan.'),
('20518', '6', 'Place 1 phyllo sheet in pan; brush with oil. Layer 3 more phyllo sheets in a row; brush each with oil. Dust with remaining Parmesan. Spoon mix over pastry; top with rest of phyllo; brush each sheet with oil. Score the top to mark off 3" x 6" pieces.'),
('20518', '7', 'Bake 35 minutes or until golden. Cool slightly; serve.Preheat oven to 350F.'),
('20518', '8', 'Heat 2 tbsp oil in a large pan on medium high heat.'),
('20518', '9', 'Add potato, onion, pepper and fennel; saut until soft, about 3 minutes.'),
('20518', '10', 'Add garlic; saut until golden, about 2 minutes. Stir in chard and spinach; cook 2 minutes or until wilted.'),
('20518', '11', 'Transfer to a bowl and cool. Beat eggs in another bowl. Stir eggs, feta, cottage cheese, soymilk, breadcrumbs, cilantro, dil,l and chives into veggie mix. Fold in crabmeat. Season with salt and pepper. Coat a 9" x 12" pan with cooking spray; dust with 2 tbsp Parmesan.'),
('20518', '12', 'Place 1 phyllo sheet in pan; brush with oil. Layer 3 more phyllo sheets in a row; brush each with oil. Dust with remaining Parmesan. Spoon mix over pastry; top with rest of phyllo; brush each sheet with oil. Score the top to mark off 3" x 6" pieces.'),
('20518', '13', 'Bake 35 minutes or until golden. Cool slightly; serve.'),
('20519', '1', 'Dried porcini mushrooms can be found in the produce section of many supermarkets and at specialty foods stores and Italian markets.'),
('20519', '2', 'Place dried porcini in a 2-cup measuring cup.'),
('20519', '3', 'Add boiling water to cover.'),
('20519', '4', 'Let soak for 30 minutes.Using a slotted spoon, transfer mushrooms to a work surface. Reserve soaking liquid. Chop mushrooms; reserve.Cook chard in a large pot of boiling salted water for 5 minutes.'),
('20519', '5', 'Transfer to a large bowl of ice water to cool.'),
('20519', '6', 'Drain; squeeze out liquid.'),
('20519', '7', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.'),
('20519', '8', 'Add leeks, onions, garlic, and a pinch each of salt and pepper. Cover and cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are soft, about 10 minutes.'),
('20519', '9', 'Add chopped crimini mushrooms, sage, and half of chopped porcini. Cook, uncovered and stirring occasionally, until crimini are soft, about 5 minutes.'),
('20519', '10', 'Place bread cubes in a large bowl.'),
('20519', '11', 'Add mushroom mixture with any liquid from pan and chard; stir to combine. Stir in Parmesan; season to taste with salt and pepper. DO AHEAD: Can be made 1 day ahead. Cover and chill stuffing, remaining porcini, and soaking liquid.'),
('20519', '12', 'Add eggs and mix well to moisten bread, adding some of reserved porcini soaking liquid to moisten if necessary (leave any sediment behind).Preheat oven to 32'),
('20519', '13', 'Combine 6 tsp. paprika, 2 Tbsp. salt, 4 tsp. sage, 4 tsp. pepper, and cardamom in a small bowl.'),
('20519', '14', 'Place veal breasts on a work surface and pound thickest part of veal with a meat mallet into even thickness. Rub spice mix all over.'),
('20519', '15', 'Spread 1 1/2 cups stuffing over each, leaving a 1" border on all sides. ('),
('20519', '16', 'Place remaining stuffing in a small baking dish and bake with veal during last 30 minutes of roasting).'),
('20519', '17', 'Roll veal into cylinders and tie crosswise with kitchen twine at 1" intervals.'),
('20519', '18', 'Heat oil in a heavy pot large enough to hold both veal breasts over medium-high heat.'),
('20519', '19', 'Add veal to pot and cook until browned on all sides, 57 minutes.'),
('20519', '20', 'Transfer veal to a large plate.'),
('20519', '21', 'Add remaining reserved porcini from stuffing, leeks, carrots, celery, and onion to pot.'),
('20519', '22', 'Add remaining 2 tsp. paprika and 1 tsp. sage; season with salt and pepper and stir to coat.'),
('20519', '23', 'Add wine, broth, and any remaining porcini soaking liquid. Boil for 2 minutes.'),
('20519', '24', 'Add veal. (Liquid should come halfway up sides of veal; add more broth if necessary).Cover, transfer to oven, and cook, basting and rotating veal every hour, until very tender, 2 1/23 hours, depending on thickness of veal.'),
('20519', '25', 'Transfer veal breasts to a carving board; tent loosely with foil.Meanwhile, spoon fat from surface of sauce. Strain sauce into a saucepan.'),
('20519', '26', 'Transfer vegetables to a blender; pure until smooth, adding some sauce as necessary.'),
('20519', '27', 'Add 2 cups pured vegetables to sauce in pan. Simmer over medium-high heat until reduced to 4 cups, 810 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper. Set aside 3 cups for veal and reserve the remaining 1 cup sauce for another use.Slice veal into 3/4"1"-thick slices and serve with sauce.'),
('20525', '1', 'Preheat oven to 400F. Rinse chicken pieces with cool water and pat dry. Season on all sides with salt and pepper.'),
('20525', '2', 'In a Dutch oven, melt butter with oil over medium heat. When foam subsides, cook chicken, working in batches if necessary, turning often, until golden, about 10 minutes.'),
('20525', '3', 'Transfer to a plate.'),
('20525', '4', 'Pour off all but 1 Tbsp. fat.'),
('20525', '5', 'Add vegetables; cook, stirring often, until slightly softened, about 2 minutes.'),
('20525', '6', 'Pour in wine and cook, scraping up any browned bits, until liquid has almost evaporated, 30 seconds to 1 minute.'),
('20525', '7', 'Add broth, garlic and rosemary. Season with salt and pepper and bring to a boil.'),
('20525', '8', 'Return chicken, skin side up, and any accumulated juices to pot. Cover and bake for 20 minutes.'),
('20525', '9', 'Remove cover; bake until juices have slightly reduced and garlic is very soft, about 30 minutes. (If mixture looks dry, add up to 1/2 cup broth.)'),
('20525', '10', 'Transfer chicken to a serving platter. Use a fork to crush a few of the softened garlic cloves. Spoon sauce and vegetables over chicken and serve immediately.'),
('20527', '1', 'Watch how to make this recipe.'),
('20527', '2', 'Heat the oil in a heavy large pot over medium heat.'),
('20527', '3', 'Add the onion, carrots, celery, pancetta, and garlic.'),
('20527', '4', 'Saute until the onion is translucent, about 10 minutes.'),
('20527', '5', 'Add the Swiss chard and potato; saute for 2 minutes.'),
('20527', '6', 'Add the tomatoes and rosemary sprig. Simmer until the chard is wilted and the tomatoes break down, about 10 minutes.'),
('20527', '7', 'Meanwhile, blend 3/4 cup of the beans with 1/4 cup of the broth in a processor until almost smooth.'),
('20527', '8', 'Add the pureed bean mixture, remaining broth, and Parmesan cheese rind to the vegetable mixture. Simmer until the potato pieces are tender, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes. Stir in the whole beans and parsley. Simmer until the beans are heated through and the soup is thick, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, to taste. Discard Parmesan rind and rosemary sprig (the leaves will have fallen off of the stem.)'),
('20527', '9', 'Ladle the soup into bowls and serve.'),
('20530', '1', 'In a cast iron skillet, cook onions in olive oil over medium-high heat until they begin to brown. Stir in brown sugar, and continue cooking for a few minutes.'),
('20530', '2', 'When onions are brown and tender, stir in chard and olives. Cook until chard is slightly wilted. Stir in capers and salt, and continue cooking until chard is completely wilted, about 3 minutes. Season with black pepper and squeeze lemon over the top.'),
('20532', '1', 'Season the short ribs with 1 tablespoon thyme and the cracked black pepper. Use your hands to coat the meat well. Cover, and refrigerate overnight.'),
('20532', '2', 'Take the short ribs out of the refrigerator an hour before cooking, to come to room temperature. After 30 minutes, season them generously on all sides with salt.'),
('20532', '3', 'When you take the ribs out of the refrigerator, preheat the oven to 425F.'),
('20532', '4', 'Toss the pearl onions with 2 tablespoons olive oil, 1 teaspoon thyme,  teaspoon salt, and a pinch of pepper.'),
('20532', '5', 'Spread them on a baking sheet and roast them about 15 minutes, until tender. When they have cooled, slip off the skins with your fingers and set aside. Turn the oven down to 325F.'),
('20532', '6', 'When its time to cook the short ribs, heat a large saut pan over high heat for 3 minutes.'),
('20532', '7', 'Pour in 3 tablespoons olive oil, and wait a minute or two, until the pan is very hot and almost smoking.'),
('20532', '8', 'Place the short ribs in the pan, and sear until they are nicely browned on all three meaty sides. Depending on the size of your pan, you might have to sear the meat in batches. Do not crowd the meat or get lazy or rushed at this step; it will take at least 15 minutes. When the ribs are nicely browned, transfer them to a braising pan. They should lie flat, bones standing up, in one layer.'),
('20532', '9', 'Turn the heat down to medium, and add the onion, carrot, celery, thyme sprigs, and bay leaves. Stir with a wooden spoon, scraping up all the crusty bits in the pan. Cook 6 to 8 minutes, until the vegetables just begin to caramelize.'),
('20532', '10', 'Add the balsamic vinegar, port, and red wine. Turn the heat up to high, and reduce the liquid by half.'),
('20532', '11', 'Add the stock and bring to a boil.'),
('20532', '12', 'Pour the liquid over the short ribs, scraping any vegetables that have fallen on the ribs back into the liquid. The stock mixture should almost cover the ribs. Tuck the parsley sprigs in and around the meat. Cover tightly with aluminum foil and a tight-fitting lid if you have one. Braise in the oven for about 3 hours.'),
('20532', '13', 'To check the meat for doneness, remove the lid and foil, being careful of the escaping steam, and pierce a short rib with a paring knife. When the meat is done, it will yield easily to a knife. Taste a piece if you are not sure.'),
('20532', '14', 'Let the ribs rest 10 minutes in their juices, and then transfer them to a baking sheet.'),
('20532', '15', 'Turn the oven up to 400F.'),
('20532', '16', 'Place the short ribs in the oven for 10 to 15 minutes, to brown.'),
('20532', '17', 'Strain the broth into a saucepan, pressing down on the vegetables with a ladle to extract all the juices. Skim the fat from the sauce and, if the broth seems thin, reduce it over medium-high heat to thicken slightly. Taste for seasoning.'),
('20532', '18', 'Heat a large saut pan over high heat for 2 minutes. Tear the Swiss chard into large pieces.'),
('20532', '19', 'Add 3 tablespoons olive oil to the pan, and stir in the cooked pearl onions.'),
('20532', '20', 'Add half the Swiss chard, and cook a minute or two, stirring the greens in the oil to help them wilt.'),
('20532', '21', 'Add a splash of water and the second half of the greens. Season with a heaping a teaspoon salt and a pinch of ground black pepper. Cook for a few more minutes, stirring frequently, until the greens are tender.'),
('20532', '22', 'Place the Swiss chard on a large warm platter, and arrange the short ribs on top. Spoon lots of braising juices over the ribs.'),
('20532', '23', 'Serve the hot potato pure and horseradish cream on the side.'),
('20533', '1', 'Bring the water to a boil in a large soup pot and add 5 teaspoons of salt.'),
('20533', '2', 'Whisk in the cornmeal in a thin, slow stream. Stir continuously for 2 minutes. Cover and reduce heat to a lively simmer. Stir one minute out of every minutes for a total of forty minutes, then uncover and cook for five more minutes. It should be creamy and thick at this point. Keep it hot until you are ready to assemble the dish, otherwise it will set up.Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat 2 tablespoons of the olive oil over a medium high flame. Fry the onion and garlic for 1 minute.'),
('20533', '3', 'Add the thinly sliced chard stems and saute for 3 minutes.'),
('20533', '4', 'Add the leaves. It is ok if they are still wet. You may have to add them in batches to get them all in the pot, waiting til the first bunch "melts" a little.'),
